Thulani Gqirana, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A Johannesburg man was hijacked, but got his car back hours later when he spotted it at a roadblock, police said on Saturday.&nbsp;The man was hijacked in Ivory Park, Johannesburg on Friday, and the two suspects dropped him off in a nearby veld, police spokesperson Captain Kay Makhubele said on Saturday.&nbsp; The victim, who had hitched a ride in a taxi, spotted his car at a roadblock while heading to the police station. &ldquo;He ran to the traffic cops and told them it was his car. He explained he had hijacked and left in a veld,&rdquo; Makhubele said. The hijacked man explained that the suspects had stolen his watch and other items, which were found on the two suspects when they were searched. &ldquo;An unlicensed firearm was also found on the two suspects, who were arrested on the spot,&rdquo; he said. They would be charged with hijacking and possession of an unlicensed firearm. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.